        <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
            <head>Biographical Note</head>
            <p><!-- BIOGHIST REQUIRED -->Movie and television director. Florey (1900-1979) was born
                in France and went to Hollywood in 1921. His two most famous movies were THE MURDERS
                IN THE RUE MORGUE and THE BEAST WITH FIVE FINGERS. In addition Florey directed
                hundreds of television shows in the 1950s of which this collection contains a
                selection.</p>
            <p/>
        </bioghist>
        <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
            <head>Scope and Content</head>
            <p>Mimeograph or multilith copies of typewritten scripts with hand-written notations for
                such series as "Four Star Playhouse," "Schlitz Playhouse," "Alcoa-Goodyear
                Anthology," and "The Texan." There are also some scripts for Walt Disney
                Productions.</p>
            <p/>
        </scopecontent>
        <arrangement encodinganalog="351">
            <head>Arrangement</head>
            <p>This collection is arranged in one series:<list type="simple">
                    <item>Series I: Scripts</item>
                </list>
            </p>
            <p>Alphabetical by title with series and writer's name given when known.</p>
        </arrangement>
